body:
@chrisduerr I think there is no method in `winit` to do it properly atm. The required method to perform `minimize` on `macOs` is [this one](https://developer.apple.com/documentation/appkit/nswindow/1419426-miniaturize?language=objc) ([rust binding for it](https://github.com/servo/cocoa-rs/blob/ea0667fdd2cffbdc442e50bbf6a2977ba7c2d322/src/appkit.rs#L1018)), which is not used in `winit` anywhere. The `minimize` and `hide` actions are different on `macOs`, we already have binding and action for `Hide`, however adding proper `macOs` `minimize` support requires a patch to `winit`.

The patch to `winit` should be very simple, it's about calling mentioned methods on `NSWindow`.

However, I can be wrong about it though.
